    "FASadrmomtazi et al. [42] found that using FA at a 30% replacement level led to micro-cracks, a 30% increase in voids, and the presence of partially reacted particles, making the matrix 15% less dense than one without FA.",
    "At a 40% replacement level, the matrix became 20% denser after 180 days, with ettringite needles replacing spherical FA particles.",
    "observed that combining FA with other materials, such as (HFFA) and Class F FA, at 5% to 15% replacement levels resulted in severe cracking and a 20% reduction in density, especially in samples with higher HFFA these finds by Georgiou et al. [59] content.",
    "Figure 6 presents an SEM photo demonstrating the impact of (FA) on the concrete microstructure.",
    "Kanthe et al. [61] discovered that incorporating RHA into concrete, particularly when combined with superplasticizers (SP), enhances particle packing density."
